03/31/83  substr

Syntax:  substr STR I {N}


Syntax as active function:  [substr STR I {N}]


Function:  returns the portion of STR starting with the character in
position I and continuing for N characters (where I and N are decimal
integers; I must be greater than zero and N must be greater than or
equal to zero).  If N is omitted, the remainder of STR is returned.  If
I is greater than the length of STR, the null string is returned.  If N
is greater than the remainder of STR, the remainder is returned.
